description:
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work within an integrated team to proactively manage, co-ordinate and support an identified caseload of approximately 50 patients with multiple complex long term conditions, with responsibility for ensuring all health and social care needs are met to improve health outcomes, functional status and quality of life, ensure integration of all elements of care, increase patient choice and prevent unnecessary admissions to hospital and reduce the stay of necessary hospital admissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rated as ‘Outstanding’ in our most recent CQC inspection, we have created a positive culture where staff feel valued and which demonstrates a genuine commitment to engaging service users, learning from experience and involving all staff in service development and innovation. So, if you recognise yourself in these requirements, we would recommend you apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to answer any questions that you may have. Please don’t hesitate to contact Mandy Hennessey on mandy.hennessey@berkshire.nhs.uk or 07717507380 for more information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMandy HennesseyAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mandy Hennessey&lt;/p&gt;
